## Status Vocabulary

| Status        | Used by         | Meaning                                                  |
|---------------|-----------------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| `draft`       | Feature spec    | Not yet approved; do not generate a plan                 |
| `approved`    | Feature spec    | Ready for plan generation                                |
| `implemented` | Feature spec    | All P0 capabilities verified                             |
| `deprecated`  | Feature spec    | No longer in scope; preserved for history                |
| `todo`        | Plan task       | Eligible for `/continue-tasks` pickup                    |
| `in-progress` | Plan task       | Task file exists in `docs/tasks/active/`                 |
| `done`        | Plan task       | Completion sentinel observed; task archived              |
| `blocked`     | Plan task       | Failure escalated to user; do not auto-retry             |

---

## Priority Vocabulary

| Tag    | Meaning                                                |
|--------|--------------------------------------------------------|
| `[P0]` | Launch-blocking. Must be in the first merged version.  |
| `[P1]` | High value. Targeted for next iteration after launch.  |
| `[P2]` | Nice to have. Backlog candidate.                       |
| `[P3]` | Speculative / research. Not yet committed.             |

---

## Failure Budget

The Error Recovery Loop (in `project-manager:continue-tasks`) tolerates up to **5 failures per plan** before escalating to the user. Each failure adds 1-3 corrective tasks rather than retrying the failed task blindly. After 5 failures, the plan is paused and a detailed issue is written to `docs/issues/`.
